(1, 17, 3, 'Rs.20 LPA ', '65% in 10th, 12th, B. Tech. (till 5th Semester aggregate) with No Backlog History ', 'Software Development Engineer', 'Online Test', 'Coding and Aptitude test.\r\nThis is an elimination round.\r\nQuestions were MCQ, Response, and Coding based.\r\nThis round contains two sections.\r\nSection 1- This section contains Aptitude Questions.\r\nSection 2- This section contains Coding & DBMS related.\r\n*Aptitude, verbal ability, and logical reasoning.\r\n*DBMS\r\n*Coding\r\n', '2 Hr', 'TECHNICAL INTERVIEW', 'How do you enforce relational integrity in database design?\r\nWhen is it appropriate to de-normalize database design?\r\nWhat is the difference between OLAP and OLTP? When is each used?\r\nWhat automated-build tools or processes have you used?\r\nWhat is the role of continuous integration systems in the automated-build process?\r\nDescribe the difference between optimistic and pessimistic locking.\r\nIn databases, what is the difference between a delete statement and a truncate statement?\r\nWhat are transaction logs, and how are they used?\r\nWhat are the most important database performance metrics, and how do you monitor them?\r\nWhat development tools have you used?\r\nWhat languages have you programmed in?\r\nWhat source control tools have you used?\r\nDescribe the elements of an in-tier architecture and their appropriate use.\r\nCompare and contrast REST and SOAP web services.\r\nDefine authentication and authorization and the tools that are used to support them in enterprise deployments.\r\nHave you used Visual Studio?\r\nHave you used Eclipse?\r\nWhat is a SAN, and how is it used?\r\nWhat is clustering, and describe its use?\r\nWhat is the role of the DMZ in network architecture?\r\n', '30 Min.', 'HR Interview', '1. Conversational skills were tested.\r\n\r\n2. Prioritizing things, situational questions were asked.\r\n', '30 Min.', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'Approved', 'https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/\r\nhttps://www.codechef.com/\r\nhttps://www.hackerrank.com/', '2022-02-25 18:53:23', 7, '2022', 'Eligibility criteria to be added\r\nThere were two profiles, only one is mentioned , check email from CRPC for resolution of it'),
(2, 18, 1, 'Rs. 9 LPA ', 'B.tech ', 'Product Engineer', 'Video making on a series of questions.', 'Video making on-\r\n\r\nWrite a program to print the pattern.\r\nWrite a program to check whether a number is prime or not.\r\nWrite a program to print first N prime number.\r\nWrite a program to print Fibonacci Series.\r\nWrite a program to count digits till N.\r\nWrite a program to print reverse of a number.\r\nWrite a program to print inverse of a string.\r\nWrite a program to rotate a number.\r\nWrite a program to find GCD & LCM of given numbers.\r\nWrite a program to find factorial of a number.\r\nWrite a program to check whether the given numbers are Pythagorean Triplet or not.\r\nWrite a program for the Curious Case of  Benjamin Bulb.\r\n', 'One Week', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'Approved', 'https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/\r\nhttps://www.codechef.com/\r\nhttps://www.hackerrank.com/', '2022-02-25 18:57:18', 7, '2022', '\r\n\r\nCapitalization error to be checked in \"Till\" Prime No. Till N\r\n\r\nJob description to be editted'),
(3, 19, 3, 'Rs. 7.37 LPA', ' Current Degree (B.Tech/MCA/M.Tech) - 70% without any backlog', 'Associate Software Engineer', 'Online Test', 'Coding and Aptitude Test.\r\nThis is an elimination round.\r\nQuestions were MCQ, Response and Coding based.\r\nThis round contains two sections.\r\nSection 1-\r\nThis section contains Aptitude Questions.\r\nSection 2-\r\nThis section contains Coding & DBMS related questions.\r\n*Aptitude, verbal ability and logical reasoning.\r\n*DBMS\r\n*Coding', '2 Hr.', 'Technical Interview', 'Explain what is Backbone.js collections ?\r\nIn databases, what is the difference between a delete statement and a truncate statement?\r\nWhat are transaction logs, and how are they used?\r\nWhat are the most important database performance metrics, and how do you monitor them?\r\nWhat development tools have you used?\r\nWhat languages have you programmed in?\r\nWhat source control tools have you used?\r\nWhat is a SAN, and how is it used?\r\nWhat is clustering, and describe its use?\r\nExplain what is Backbone.js router is used for ?\r\nExplain what is Backbone.js Models?\r\nWhat is model.attributes ?\r\nWhat is the function of toJSON ?\r\nMention what are the types of Notation used for Time Complexity?\r\nExplain how binary search works?\r\nExplain what is Skip list?', '30 Min.', 'HR Interview', '1. Introduce yourself. Why do you choose OPTUM? Do you have any location preference? Do you have any questions?\r\n2. Are you ready to relocate? What is your weakness and what are the ways to overcome it?\r\n3. What do you know about Optum?What are your strengths? How much marks you got in 10th,12th and your semester exams?\r\n4. What is the biggest challenge in your life and how will you overcome that challenge?\r\n\r\n', '30 Min.', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'Approved', 'https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/\r\nhttps://www.codechef.com/\r\nhttps://www.hackerrank.com/', '2022-02-25 19:15:18', 7, '2022', 'Introduce yourself. Why OPTUM? Location preference. Any questions?\r\n2. Ready to relocate? Weakness and ways to overcome it. \r\n3. How did you hear about Optum? Your strengths? your marks?\r\n4. Biggest challenge in life and how you overcome the challenge.\r\n\r\nFrame proper questions \r\nEligibility Criteria: Current Degree (B.Tech/MCA/M.Tech) - 70% without any backlog\r\n.Eligility :Tech (CSE, CS, CSI, IT, EC, EEE, EI), MCA, and M.Tech 2022 Batch Female students '),
