(5, 20, 4, ' Rs. 19 LPA', 'B.Tech (CSE,CS,IT,CSI,EC)', 'Associate Software Engineer & Associate Analyst', 'Online Test', 'Coding and Aptitude test.\r\nThis is an elimination round.\r\nAll questions were MCQ-based.\r\nThis round contains two sections.\r\nSection 1-\r\nThis section contains Aptitude Questions.\r\nSection 2-\r\nThis section contains Technical Questions related to the core.\r\nQuestions from subjects like thermodynamics, material science, industrial management, and manufacturing mainly.\r\nAptitude, verbal ability, and logical reasoning.\r\n', '2 Hr.', 'Coding', 'Questions based on AVL-Tree\r\nQuestions based on Game Theory \r\nQuestions based on OOP\r\nQuestions based on DFS\r\nQuestions based on Divide and Conquer\r\n', '90 Min.', 'Technical Interview', 'TECHNICAL QUESTIONS\r\n\r\nQuestions based on OOPS concept.\r\nWhat is wrapper class in java?\r\nDefine Friend function in c++.\r\nWhat is Constructor and list its types.\r\nWhat is Dynamic polymorphism?\r\nDefine Constructor Overloading.\r\nTell me something about MongoDB.\r\nWhat is the difference between SQL and no SQL databases?\r\nWhat are indexes? What are its uses ? Give a real-world example. \r\nWhat is the primary key? What is a foreign key? What problems does foreign key solve? What are data anomalies? \r\nWhat is a garbage collector in java? Can we explicitly call GC? What is the command for it? \r\nWhat is a linked list? Difference between array and linked list. \r\nGive an example of real-world programming where a linked list is used over an array.\r\nWhat is JVM?\r\nWhat are the latest technological trends and how are you keeping up with them? \r\nPuzzle-type Questions.\r\nWhat are pointers? Why Java doesn\'t support pointers? \r\nWhat are dangling pointers and How do you fix them? \r\nDiscussion about dynamic memory allocation (malloc, calloc, realloc). \r\nWhat do you know about inheritance? What are multiple & multilevel inheritances?  Why java doesn\'t support multiple inheritances? 