(65, 37, 3, 'Rs. 4 LPA', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Percentage Screening\r\nEnrollment Form\r\n\r\n', '0', 'N/A', 'Platform\r\nHireVue (Online platform for virtual video interviewing, recruiting and hiring)\r\nMode: \r\nOnline video-based assessment\r\nType: Elimination Round\r\n\r\nPractice (optional):\r\n3 questions (3mins for question + 3 mins for answering)\r\nMultiple retakes to get accustomed to the platform.\r\nQuestion level - easy.\r\nMain Test:\r\n3 questions (3mins for question + 3 mins for answering)\r\nOnly two attempts were allowed.\r\nQuestion level: Moderate\r\n1 Technical Question + 2 Situation-Based Questions (Case study)\r\nNote: \r\nTechnical questions can be from any other branch. (ME, EEE, EI)\r\nSet A: \r\nA warehouse is located 40 km from the production unit. State the advantages and disadvantages of the same. \r\nDuring COVID-19 the production unit of Sanitizers and Disinfectants is in the contamination zone. How would you manage the workers’ shift? \r\nQuestion related to Boilers by using supplementary fuel, cost-cutting, and efficiency.\r\nA production centre is relocated 40km away from the current centre. What factors will it cause on the production and how will you manage the effects faced by the various workers working at that centre?\r\n\r\nSet B:\r\n10k trucks are managed by a third party to facilitate movement between production units and warehouses. Suggest a way to get cost-cutting and better efficiency. .\r\nQuestion related to Boiler by using supplementary fuel, cost-cutting and efficiency. \r\nA boiler has a steam capacity of 4tons/hr. We have a biomass of 12 tons which can produce 40 tons of steam. As a byproduct methane gas is coming out of the system which is highly utilized for heating the water for making an efficient system. Find the amount of energy produced by the secondary medium and the cost-effectiveness.\r\nGiven-\r\nGCV of methane = 55530 kJ/kg, GCV of biomass = 15170 kJ/kg, Volume of methane gas = 500m3, Cost of biomass = Rs 5.2/kg \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSet C:\r\nWhat is the impact of the covid-19 pandemic on FMCG companies? How do you increase productivity? Give possible reasons.\r\nHow will you improve the security of our drivers who work on long projects? Give an example considering the 6 sigma principle.\r\nA numerical of a power plant. In which we have to calculate the amount of energy-saving and saving amount per year.\r\nA hair care product has launched successfully in the USA. For launching the same product in India, which marketing strategies should be applied?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Platform:\r\n MS - Teams (Link shared via mail after confirmation overcall)\r\nMode: Online video-based assessment\r\nType: Elimination Round\r\nPanel: 1 Assessor allotted (2 assessors present for 2 candidates)\r\nDuration: 30 min allotted slot (Avg. time – 17-18 min)\r\nAssessment: HR\r\nIntroduce yourself.\r\nWhy HUL?\r\nWhere do you see yourself 5 years down the line?\r\nIf work assigned to you is not related to instrumentation, then how will you tackle that, will you agree to work?\r\nQuestion level: easy to moderate.\r\nYou are in charge of a production unit’s night shift. During a tea break at night, workers show anomalous behavior and refuse to work stating that the tea is not good. How will you manage the situation in absence of your seniors?\r\nYou are in charge of a production unit’s night shift. During the night a machine develops an electrical fault. Knowing the severity of the fault, if you run the machine it might catch fire and the lives of workers could be at risk. However, this has not happened in past years. Shutting down the production might incur losses worth crores. What will be your response and how will you manage the situation?\r\nAre you willing to work night shifts?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTechnical:\r\nIt consists of the major part of the interview.\r\nQuestion level – moderate to hard.\r\nQuestions based on basic knowledge from the branch.\r\nQuestions from Study subjects, Project, Industrial Visit, and Internship.\r\nMajor subjects covered in the interview were Industrial Measuring Instruments, Sensors, and Transducers. (from EI branch)\r\nWhat is the functioning of Ammeter? Why can’t we use it in parallel?\r\nDo you know about the Galvanometer? On which principle does it work? Also, explain its functioning.\r\nWhat is a Potentiometer? Explain its types, functions, and industrial applications.\r\nDo you know about Thermocouples? Explain its principle.\r\nRelation between deflecting torque and controlling torque.\r\nWhat are resistance, inductance, and capacitance? What are their units?\r\nWhat are transducers? What are its types?\r\nWhat do you understand about inverse transducers?\r\nQuestions related to project work-\r\nQuestion-based on components of the project.\r\nExplain the functioning of Servo motors. What are its industrial applications?\r\nWhat are motors? What do you understand about stepper motors?\r\nWhich motor is used in a 3D printer?\r\nWhat are Flex Sensors? How have you used them to copy hand gestures?\r\nQuestions based on Industrial Visit-\r\nWhich place and departments of the place you visited?\r\nWhat were the measuring instruments you observed?\r\nWhat were the safety measures used in boilers?\r\nMore emphasis on practical and applications aspects than theory.\r\nQuestions are asked in succession to the answer given.\r\nNo cross questionings, questions were more of a rapid-fire type.\r\nNote: Technical question tests in-depth knowledge of candidates with practical and applications-based concepts.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '30 MIN', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'N/A', 'Pending Approval', 'N/A', '2022-02-25 00:00:00', 11, '0', NULL),
