(77, 66, 3, '14 LPA-18 LPA', 'The participating student should have completed at least either (one) of the below from the Netacad courses:  CCNA Module 1 + Python / Networking Essentials + Python, or DevNet', 'Cyber Security', 'Online Test', 'This round contains 2 sections –\r\nSECTION 1- This section contains MCQ based on verbal ability, logical reasoning, numerical reasoning, and soft skills.\r\n---------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nSECTION 2- This section contains coding questions.', '90', 'Technical', '1. Tell me briefly about your IDEATHON idea.\r\n2. What is the function of the Networking layer in the Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) model?\r\n3. Explain Quick Sort.\r\n4. What is the PING command used for?\r\n5. What is TTL (time to live) in PING command?\r\n6. Write a code to check if a given String is a Palindrome or not.\r\n7. What is a Network?\r\n8. What is a Node?\r\n9. What are Routers?\r\n10. What is the Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) reference model?\r\n11.  What are the layers in Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) Reference Models? Describe each layer briefly.\r\n12. What is the difference between Hub, Switch, and Router?\r\n13.  Explain TCP (Transmission Control Protocol)/IP (Internet Protocol) Model.\r\n14. What is HTTPS and what port does it use?\r\n15. What are Transmission Control Protocol (TCP) and UDP?\r\n16. What is a Firewall?\r\n17. What is a Domain Name Server (DNS)?\r\n18. What are IP (Internet Protocol) classes and how can you identify the IP (Internet Protocol) class of a given IP (Internet Protocol) address?\r\n19.  What is meant by 127.0.0.1 and localhost?\r\n20. Explain Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP) briefly.\r\n21. What is the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP)?\r\n22. Expand Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP) and describe how it works.\r\n23. Expand SLIP?\r\n24. Define IEEE in the networking world.\r\n25. Why is the standard of an Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) model termed 802.xx?\r\n', '40 mins-60mins', 'HR', '1. Why do you want to join Cisco?\r\n2. If a teammate falls sick in the middle of a project, would you give him credit for work done after the end of the project?\r\n3. How would you handle a team member that was not pulling their weight? What would you say to them?\r\n4. You have hackathon experience as a leader. What problems did you face, and how did you tackle them?\r\n5. Tell me about yourself (keep it short).\r\n6. Tell me about all the internships you have done.\r\n7. Are you ready for relocation?\r\n8. Are you comfortable with the night shift?\r\n9. If you have to work on three projects with different timestamps based on the timing of different countries, how are you going to manage it?\r\n10. Do you have any person from whom you have taken inspiration apart from your family members?\r\n11. How will you motivate yourself if the work that is given is not related to your domain, and you are bound to do it?\r\n12. If you have to lead a team of 3 people and you have to make them work on a project that has a total of 10 modules, then how are you going to assign the tasks to the team members?\r\n13. If a team member denies doing the assigned work, how are you going to convince him to do it?\r\n14. What do you know about the job role?\r\n15. What do you know about Cisco?\r\n16. What do you know about Cisco\'s competitors?\r\n17. What is the difference between consulting and developer roles in Cisco?\r\n18. Why Cisco, and why are you interested in networking?\r\n19. Do you have any location preferences with proper reasoning? \r\n20. Why should we hire you for this job role? \r\n21. Where do you see yourself in the next 5 years?\r\n22. What are your strengths and weaknesses, with supporting examples?\r\n23. How would you rate your problem-solving skills, and why?\r\n', '40 mins-60 mins', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 'Rejected', 'https://prepinsta.com/\r\nhttps://www.glassdoor.co.in/index.htm\r\nhttps://www.geeksforgeeks