(84, 67, 3, '3.96 LPA, 7.2 LPA', '60% throughout', 'TCS Ninja, TCS Digital', 'Coding Test', 'This round contains 6 coding questions.', '6 Hours', 'Technical', '1. What is your primary programming language?\r\n2. Why did you choose Python as your first language?\r\n3. Tell me something you know about Java.\r\n4. Why did you not select Java as a language?\r\n5. Difference between Java and Python.\r\n6. If you are standing in the north direction and move some distance to the right and then some distance to the left, which direction will you end up in?\r\n7. Explain the projects you have done and brief us about the technologies used in them.\r\n8. Where is the headquarters of TCS?\r\n9. What is Spring Boot?\r\n10. Which Data Structure is stable?\r\n11. What is Depth First Search?\r\n12. How will you Detect cycles in a graph?\r\n13. Explain Array and linked list.\r\n14. Write a program to find the LCM of three numbers.\r\n15. Explain pillars of OOPs.\r\n16. Why have you chosen C++?\r\n17. Tell us any three differences between Java and C++.\r\n18. Tell us the difference and real-life examples of data structures like stack and queue.\r\n19. Explain Inheritance with its different types.\r\n20. What is the difference between classes and interfaces?\r\n21. What is the approach used by you in solving questions in coding?  ', '40-60 minutes', 'HR', '1. Tell me about yourself.\r\n2. Which sports do you like the most?\r\n3. What traits of your favorite sportsman do you like and how does it help you in your life?\r\n4. How often do you travel, and do you prefer to travel with your friends or family?\r\n5. Tell me something about your weakness and strength?\r\n6. Which person inspires you the most?\r\n7. Why TCS?\r\n8. You have heard many things about TCS from your family, friends etc. So, what do you not like about TCS?\r\n9. What is the quality of a leader?\r\n10. What is the difference between a learner and an experienced person?\r\n11. What are your hobbies?\r\n12. Why did you 