(86, 64, 3, '3.5 LPA, 5.5 LPA', '60% throughout', 'Associate Software Engineer', 'MCQ', 'This round consists of 2 sections:\r\n\r\nSection 1: This section contains MCQ based on Quantitative Aptitude, Logical reasoning and Verbal Ability and Computer fundamentals.\r\n\r\nSection 2: This section contains coding questions.\r\n\r\nCODING QUESTIONS:\r\n1.	Write a program for calculating and returning the sums of the absolute differences between adjacent numbers in arrays of positive integers. This must be calculated from the position determined by the current user. In the case of this coding problem, you use three positional arguments and find Total Sum function. The three inputs you would require are the number of elements inside the array, the elements in the array, and the position from which this function will take place. For example, suppose the total number of elements is 5, and these are the elements: 1 2 3 6 4 Then, if we decide to start from the 3rd position or enter 3 as input, the function will occur at ‘3’, the 3rd number in the array. Hence, the sum would be a total of (6-3)+(4-6)= 5\r\n2.	Write a program that will allow you to find out how many clothing pieces in total of a certain length can be extracted from a particular number of cloth pieces. We can estimate the required length for each clothing piece as 10 feet. In this case, we must first decide on the length unit as feet and determine the inputs we need. For this function, we will need two inputs: first the number of pieces (in the array), and the size of each piece in feet inside the array. A cloth merchant has some pieces of cloth of different lengths. He has an order of curtains of length 12 feet. He needs to find out how many curtains can be made from these pieces. The length of pieces of cloth is recorded in feet. For example, suppose the total number of elements is 3,and these are the elements: 0 10 40. Then, the first input is 3 followed by the second input of 0, 10, and 40. Hence, the sum would be a total of 0 + (10/10) + (40/10) = 5th Us, there could be 5 pieces of clothing extracted from these 3 pieces of cloth of variable sizes.', '3', 'Coding Round', '1.	Can we overload the main function in Java?\r\n2.	Write a program to print pattern 1 1 2 4 3 9.\r\n3.	Write a Program for String reverse.\r\n4.	In the C++, language write a program to share the screen and write the syntax of string comparison and the syntax of Polymorphism types.\r\n5.	Write a program to implement an algorithm to find Armstrong’s number. \r\n6.	What is the difference between the Primary Key and the Foreign key?\r\n7.	What is the difference between Polymorphism and Inheritance?\r\n8.	What are Static variables?\r\n9.	What is Inheritance and what are its types?\r\n10.	Explain the OOPs (Object Oriented Programming) concept.\r\n11.	What is File Handling?', '40-60 minutes', 'HR', '1.	Tell me about your projects.\r\n2.	What is your minor and primary goal, and how will this company help you achieve that?\r\n3.	Are you familiar with new technologies that meet the requirement?\r\n4.	Will you be able to relocate?\r\n5.	Where do you see yourself in the next 5 years?\r\n6.	Is the growth of technology suitable for humans?\r\n7.	Would you prefer hard work or smart work?\r\n8.	Who is your inspiration?\r\n9.	Why did you choose this field?\r\n10.	What do you know about the job role?\r\n11.	Tell me about your family background.\r\n12.	Are you happy with the package offered?\r\n13.	Describe yourself in three words.\r\n14.	What is your strength?\r\n15.	What is your weakness?', '40-60 minutes', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', 'Approved', 'Prepinsta- https://prepinsta.com\r\nGfg - https://www.geeksforgeeks.org\r\nIndiabix - https://www.indiabix.com\r\nGlassdoor- https://www.glassdoor.co.in ', '2023-04-05 07:55:06', 15, '2023', 'In eligiblity add\r\n1- 60% throughout\r\n2-not more than 1 yr gap\r\n3- no active backlog\r\nB.Tech (CSE, CS, CSI, IT, ECE)'),
(87, 9, 4, '4.25 LPA, 7.50 LPA', 'No Backlogs', ' Analyst, Analyst*, Senior Analyst', 'Online Test', 'It has three sections: - English, Technical, and Game-based Assessment, all three have section-wise cut-offs. \r\n\r\nEnglish Spoken Assessment: To test English and Communication Skills.\r\n\r\nTechnical Questions asked from: \r\n●	DBMS\r\n●	CS Fundamentals\r\n●	OOPS\r\n●	Core Fundamentals (For Core Branches)\r\n●	Soft Skill\r\n●	Array\r\n●	String\r\n●	Stack & Queue\r\n●	Dynamic Programming\r\n●	Greedy Algorithm\r\n●	Tree & Graph\r\n●	Aptitude\r\n\r\nGame-based Aptitude:\r\nThere will be a total of 24 games, out of which the system will select 4 games for you. Your task is to solve those 4 games accurately and speedily, without making as few mistakes as you can.\r\n\r\n*Who ever scored well were directed to the second round, while others went directly to the third round.\r\n', '90 mins', 'Coding Round', '1. A string is said to be a special string if either of the two conditions is met: All of the characters are the same, e.g. \'aaa\'. All characters except the middle one are the same, e.g. \'aadaa\'. A special substring is any substring of a string that meets one of those criteria. Given a string, determine how many special substrings can be formed from it?\r\n2. Given are two arrays of size n. Maximize the first array by using the elements from the second array such that the new array formed contains n greatest but unique elements of both the arrays, giving the second array priority (All elements of the second array appear before the first array). The order of appearance of elements is kept the same in output as in input.\r\n\r\n    \r\n', '40 mins-60mins', 'Communication Test', 'This section consists of grammatical and vocabulary questions, for testing your English communication skills.\r\nTopics Included:\r\n● Sentence Correction\r\n● Prepositions\r\n● Grammar\r\n● Synonyms and Antonyms\r\n● Article\r\n● Reading Comprehension\r\n● Speech and Tenses\r\n', '40 mins-60 mins', 'Technical + HR Round', 'Technical Questions\r\n\r\n1. What is the difference between Structure and Union?\r\n2. What are Data Structures?\r\n3. What is a Linked List?\r\n4. How do you present yourself as a personal brand?\r\n5. What is Function?\r\n6. What are the types of Budgets in the Industry?\r\n7. Draw a layout of an ATM machine where you can\'t withdraw money if you don\'t have enough money.\r\n8. What is a File Replica?\r\n9. What are Final, Finally, and Finalize keywords in Java?\r\n10. How does Dynamic host configuration protocol help in Network Management?\r\n11. What is an anonymous File Transfer Protocol (FTP)?\r\n12. Why should you utilize a Database Management System (DBMS)? \r\n13. Explain parallel testing in Selenium.\r\n14. What is the difference between XRANGE and RANGE in Python?\r\n15. Why are Java Strings Immutable in nature?\r\n16. What are the disadvantages of using an Array for Queue implementation?\r\n17. What is the difference between MALLOC() and NEW()?\r\n\r\n\r\nHR Questions\r\n\r\n1. Why Capgemini?\r\n2. Describe yourself in three Words.\r\n3. Why do you think Capgemini is good for you?\r\n4. What are your strengths and weaknesses?\r\n5. Take me through your resume.\r\n6. Tell me about your past projects. \r\n7. Where do you see yourself five years from now?\r\n8. How quickly do you adopt new technology?\r\n9. How do you feel about doing repetitive work?\r\n10. What are your salary expectations?\r\n11. What motivates you?\r\n12. How will you manage a team under pressure?\r\n13. What do you do when you are messed up at work?\r\n14. What are the most important things to be a role model for the team?\r\n15. Do you have any questions?\r\n', '40 mins-60 mins', ' ', 'Approved', 'https://prepinsta.com/\r\nhttps://www.glassdoor.co.in/index.htm\r\nhttps://www.geeksforgeeks.org/\r\nhttps://www.indiabix.com/', '2023-04-05 07:40:21', 12, '2023', 'In round 1 remove technical question add from section\r\nalso mention ctc as 4.25,5.75,7.5