(88, 81, 2, '4.25LPA', '70% Throughout (10th,12th & Graduation).', 'SOFTWARE ENGINEER', 'Online Test', 'There are two sections in this round. \r\n\r\nSection 1-\r\n75 MCQs based on verbal ability, logical reasoning, numerical reasoning, and soft skills\r\n\r\nSECTION 2-\r\nCoding questions\r\n \r\n1. Write a program to find out the initial Velocity, the final Velocity, Time, and Acceleration.\r\n2. Write a program to find out whether the Array was lucky or not by finding two adjacent numbers to be even or odd. If both are odd or even, then it\'s not lucky; otherwise, it is lucky.\r\n3. Implement a given Physics formula on sample inputs and print the results.\r\n4. Write a program for the standard Sliding Window problem.\r\n5. Write a program to find the sum of Even numbers.\r\n6. Write a program to find out the sides of a Triangle with the help of Pythagoras theorem.\r\n7. Write a program to find the total number of Pairs of even numbers.\r\n', '95 Minutes', 'Technical + HR', 'Technical Questions\r\n\r\n1. What is the difference between C and C++?\r\n2. What is the difference between Java and JavaScript?\r\n3. How is memory managed in Python?\r\n4. Which class is Superclass in Python?\r\n5. What is the use of Polymorphism?\r\n6. What is input-output (I/O) in C++?\r\n7. What is the difference between a Constant variable and a Global variable?\r\n8. What is the use of the pointer in C?\r\n9. What is the difference between Compiler, Interpreter, and Assembler?\r\n10. What is the role of the Domain Name System (DNS)?\r\n11. How to plot a graph in MATLAB?\r\n12. How to call a function in MATLAB?\r\n13. How to use a for loop in MATLAB?\r\n14. How to read CSV files?\r\n15. What are the types of Indexing?\r\n\r\n\r\nHR Questions\r\n\r\n\r\n1. Tell me about yourself.\r\n2. Explain your major project.\r\n3. Why do you want to join HCL?\r\n4. What is the difference between Learning and Implementation?\r\n5. Tell me about your family.\r\n6. Tell me about your life journey up until now.\r\n7. If we offer you a job, will you be able to relocate?\r\n8. What do you know about the profile you are applying for?\r\n9. What was your role in your major project?\r\n10. What will you choose: to either work in a team or work as an individual, and what were the challenges you faced while working in a team?\r\n11. Why did you choose the IT (Information Technology) sector?\r\n12. What are your opinions about students coming from other branches than Computer Science for these jobs?\r\n13. Who is your role model?\r\n14. What is your weakness?\r\n15. What are your skills?\r\n16. How do you handle stressful situations?\r\n17. Do you agree with the Company Service Agreement?\r\n18. Why are you not carrying out your internship as full-time employment?\r\n19. Tell me about your academics.\r\n20. Would you be comfortable with another domain profile in HCL than your own?\r\n21. Are you aware that your graduation percentage is at 70% after the 6th semester? So, if you fail to fulfil the criteria after the 8th semester, your candidature will be cancelled.\r\n22. Why should we hire you?\r\n23. Why didn\'t you pursue higher studies?\r\n25. Do you want to pursue an MBA after completing B.Tech?\r\n26. Situation-based question:\r\nConsider yourself a project manager. If you were previously allotted a project with a deadline of 30 days from now, but now the deadlines have been changed to 15 days, there is also a personal schedule lined up for you, as you need to confront the team with the shorter deadline as well. How will you manage your team and project? How will you handle the stress and workload?\r\n27. Why do you want to work with HCL? What motivated you to join HCL?\r\n28. Which technical languages are you proficient in?\r\n29. What are your aspirations?\r\n30. What are your hobbies?\r\n31. How are you a meritorious student?\r\n32. How will you manage if we post you in another state?\r\n33. Does bond and salary matter for you?\r\n34. What are your long-term and short-term goals?\r\n35. What is the biggest failure of your life?\r\n36. What are your leadership qualities?\r\n37. How will you tackle disputes among team members?\r\n38. Write an email to the manager asking for leave.\r\n39. Rate your communication skills out of 10.\r\n', '40 - 60 min', ' ', ' ', ' ', 'NA', ' ', 'NA', ' ', 'Approved', 'Prepinsta- https://prepinsta.com\r\nGfg - https://www.geeksforgeeks.org\r\nIndiabix - https://www.indiabix.com\r\nGlassdoor- https://www.glassdoor.co.in', '2023-04-06 07:45:49', 13, '2023', NULL);
