(89, 5, 2, '4.5 LPA, 6.5 LPA', 'No Active Backlogs and Max 1 year gap', 'Associate Software Engineer, Software Engineer', 'Online Test', 'There are two sections in this round.\r\nSection 1-\r\n\r\n90 MCQs based on verbal ability, logical reasoning, numerical reasoning, soft skills, technical ability, common applications of MS Office, pseudo code, and network security cloud.\r\n\r\nSECTION 2-\r\nCoding questions\r\n\r\n1. Reverse a Linked List in k groups, and round off the integer to its nearest multiple of 10.\r\n2. Given is an integer N, denoting the number of cards in a specific deck, and an Array arr[] of size N where i denotes the frequency of the ith type of card. Also given are K jokers. The task is to find the maximum possible valid decks with the given data. A valid deck should follow one of the two mentioned conditions:\r\n• A deck should contain exactly one card of each type and no jokers.\r\n• A deck should contain exactly one card of each type except one, and exactly one joker.\r\n3. Given an Array of positive integer numbers and a positive integer target, return the minimal length of a sub-Array whose sum is greater than or equal to the target. If there is no such sub-Array, return 0 instead.\r\n4. Calculate a*b mod 1337 where a is a positive integer and b is an extremely large positive integer given in the form of an Array.\r\n5. Given is an Array arr[] of size N. The task is to find the sum of the contiguous sub-Array within arr[] with the largest sum. \r\n6. You are climbing a staircase. It takes n steps to reach the top. At one time you can either climb 1 or 2 steps. In how many distinct ways can you climb to the top?\r\n7. Find the largest element in the Array.\r\n', '95 mins', 'Technical + HR', 'Technical Questions\r\n\r\n1. What do you know about \'Networks\' in industries?\r\n2. What kind of projects have you worked on and what responsibilities did you have?\r\n3. There is a senior in your group who is not taking the internship project seriously. How will you convince him to do the work?\r\n4. Has there been any situation where you went through hardships but overcame them?\r\n5. What is the use of the STATIC keyword in Java?\r\n6. Can we implement multiple interfaces in a single Java Class?\r\n7. What is the significance of SUPER and THIS keyword in Java?\r\n8. What is Run-Time Polymorphism and how is it achieved in Java?\r\n9. Distinguish between Array and Array-List provided by Java.\r\n10. What is the “Diamond problem” in Java?\r\n11. How can you differentiate among C, C++, and Java?\r\n12. What are Lambda expressions in Java?\r\n13. Can you differentiate between VAR++ and ++VAR?\r\n14. Explain the Memory Allocation process in C.\r\n15. Explain about GETCH() function in a C++ program. How is it different from the GETCH() function?\r\n16. What is meant by the Friend function in C++?\r\n17. What is Normalization in the database?\r\n18. Can you give the differences between PRIMARY KEY and UNIQUE KEY in SQL?\r\n19. What are Pandas in Python?\r\n20. What is a Classifier in Python?\r\n21. What is the difference between a Dictionary and a Tuple in Python?\r\n22. What is MAP() function in Python?\r\n23. What is XML?\r\n24. Write a C++ program for generating the Fibonacci series.\r\n\r\n\r\nHR Questions\r\n\r\n\r\n1. What do you know about the company?\r\n2. Tell me about your family background.\r\n3. Tell me about your weaknesses. How will you work to improve on them?\r\n4. Who is your role model and why?\r\n5. Where do you see yourself after 2 years?\r\n6. What is your goal in life?\r\n7. Why have you applied for this job?\r\n8. What is the motivating factor for you at work?\r\n9. If recruiting someone for this position, what qualities would you look for?\r\n10. You have been job-hopping in the last decade. Why is that?\r\n11. How do you handle criticism at work?\r\n12. Tell us about your work/leadership style.\r\n13. How would you handle a problem with your performance?\r\n14. How would you classify your style of management?\r\n15. How would you work through a situation where your team does not perform as expected?\r\n16. Why should I hire you?\r\n', '40 mins-60mins', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', ' ', 'Approved', 'https://prepinsta.com/\r\nhttps://www.glassdoor.co.in/index.htm\r\nhttps://www.geeksforgeeks.org/\r\nhttps://www.indiabix.com/', '2023-04-05 10:06:30', 12, '2023', 'Grammatical errors found.'),
